Outcome 1:
1.1. Two (2) business organization involved in sustainable habitat management at two (2) target PAs (Mid-Pripyat and Servech reserves );
1.2. Of the total number of experts hired by the project 53% were women (12 out of 23);
1.3. 296 ha of area of natural, highly productive foraging grounds in the Nalibоkski Reserve;
1.4. 50% of bison of micro population (about 50 individuals) have been foraging in this area (in the restored mosaic meadows) during late autumn and winter. In the early spring, though, bisons were still feeding on adjacent agricultural fields. This is explained by the fact that the formation of highly productive meadows in Belarus takes 2-3 years. It is expected that meadows created by the project in 2018-2019 will become productive in 2020-2021. The Project will monitor this process fields;
1.5. Sporovsky: 1,600 ha;  
Zvanets: 4,500 ha;
1.6. Project monitors water levels at 8 points: 
- 4 on Zvanets bog 
- 2 on Sporoskoe bog 
- 1 on Dikoe bog 
- 1 on Servech bog 
Sporovski reserve: (1) a water level of 5-20 cm above ground (optimal level) were maintained during May-July in 2019, but dropped to 10-30 cm below ground in 2020 due to regional drought related to climate change); (2) Water mineralization is from 150 to 300 mg/l (at the level of EoP target)  
Zvanets Nature Reserve: Optimal water level of 5-20 cm above ground l during May-July has been maintained.  
In 2020, due to the absence of snow in winter and a shortage of rainfall in spring, the whole Polesie region suffered from low water levels. And no spring flooding occurred this year. As a result, water level in the Sporovskoye floodplain swamp has been registered below optimal. In Zvanets swamp, thanks to a number of measures on optimizing the hydrological regime, water level is being maintained close to the optimal level. 
In 2019-2020, water levels in Dikoiye and Servech bogs were low due to low precipitation rate and snowless winter. 
No changes in mineralization rates observed. Reduction of mineralization is envisaged in the next 2-3 years after implementation of hydro optimization measures.
